        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 5:38PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Talladega, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Talladega Superspeedway, Honda Manufacturing Of Alabama, Jackson
Shoals, Talladega, Lincoln, Howells Cove, and Logan Martin Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
